race.comment: ISTOLEA MERC (1) dominated first-up over this distance at Warwick Farm then a step up to Saturday grade on a soft track didn't work out last start. Genuine gelding who reunites with Ash Morgan who has won twice on him from just four rides. Perfectly placed to make amends. BALKANS (3) closed resolutely to finish fourth in the same race as ISTOLEA MERC at Randwick last time out. Saves his best for 1100m at Canterbury so from gate one a long-awaited win is not out of the question. WAVE BREAKER (8) switched from Peter Snowden to Justin Drake before the last outing and met with immediate success in a BM82 over 1000m at Scone. Kept fresh for this as she likes it. Makes plenty of appeal from a favourable draw on the limit weight. APEX (5) is back after a 20-week spell. Opened last prep with a second under 61kgs in a BM64 over this course and distance. Recent trial winner who looks wound up for a big performance. Last start Hawkesbury winner INOUE (7) is up in grade but worth considering.
